## 6. API Contract — Agreed Request & Response Format

This is the finalized contract between frontend and backend.

**Request:**
```
POST http://localhost:5000/analyze
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "http://suspicious-site.xyz"
}
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "url": "http://suspicious-site.xyz",
  "timestamp": "2026-03-26T10:30:00Z",
  "validation": { "is_valid": true, "protocol": "http", "domain": "suspicious-site.xyz" },
  "features": { "url_length": 30, "hyphen_count": 1, "suspicious_keywords": [], "tld": ".xyz", "has_ip_address": false, "has_at_symbol": false, "subdomain_count": 0, "is_https": false, "special_char_count": 1 },
  "ml_prediction": { "score": 72, "label": "phishing", "confidence": "high" },
  "threat_intelligence": {
    "virustotal": { "found": false, "malicious_count": 0, "total_engines": 90 },
    "phishtank": { "found": false, "verified": false },
    "openphish": { "found": false }
  },
  "risk": { "score": 72, "level": "Malicious", "reasons": ["Unusual TLD (.xyz)", "Non-HTTPS connection"] }
}
```

**Error Response:**
```json
{
  "url": "http://suspicious-site.xyz",
  "timestamp": "2026-03-26T10:30:00Z",
  "error": true,
  "message": "Analysis failed at feature extraction stage."
}
```

